19Ps 47:1 (To the chief Musician, A Psalm for the sons of Korah.) O clap your hands, all ye people; shout unto God with the voice of triumph.
19Ps 47:2 For the LORD most high [is] terrible; [he is] a great King over all the earth.
19Ps 47:3 He shall subdue the people under us, and the nations under our feet.
19Ps 47:4 He shall choose our inheritance for us, the excellency of Jacob whom he loved. Selah.
19Ps 47:5 God is gone up with a shout, the LORD with the sound of a trumpet.
19Ps 47:6 Sing praises to God, sing praises: sing praises unto our King, sing praises.
19Ps 47:7 For God [is] the King of all the earth: sing ye praises with understanding.
19Ps 47:8 God reigneth over the heathen: God sitteth upon the throne of his holiness.
19Ps 47:9 The princes of the people are gathered together, [even] the people of the God of Abraham: for the shields of the earth [belong] unto God: he is greatly exalted.
